==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[άνθρωπος]]''' (''anthropos'') "man, mankind, [[human]], humanity" (''from '''[[ανήρ]]''' (aner) "man" + '''[[ώπς]]''' (ops) "the eye, the face, countenance"'') + '''[[λόγος]]''' see "[[logos]]".

===Noun===
'''anthropology'''

# the [[holistic]] scientific and social study of [[humanity]]

====Derived terms====
* [[anthropologic]], or [[anthropological]]
* [[anthropologist]]
* [[cultural anthropology]]
* [[paleoanthropology]]

